-- Usage facts without checkers parse as reserved names and are rejected, so no
-- program can give a reserved fact a meaning. (`noalloc`, `once`, `portable`,
-- and `noescape` are checked; `unique` stands in for the reserved set.)
fn apply(f : ((Int) -> Int) @ unique, x : Int) : Int = f(x)

fn main() : Int = apply(\(y) -> y + 1, 41)
